<H1><A =
href=3D"http://osrin.net/2008/05/openxmldaisyxml-translator-now-available=
/"=20
rel=3Dbookmark>OpenXML/DaisyXML Translator Now Available</A></H1>
<P>Posted on May 7, 2008<BR>Filed Under <A title=3D"View all posts in =
General"=20
href=3D"http://osrin.net/category/general/" rel=3D"category =
tag">General</A>, <A=20
title=3D"View all posts in Standards" =
href=3D"http://osrin.net/category/standards/"=20
rel=3D"category tag">Standards</A> | </P>
<P><A =
href=3D"http://osrin.net/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/daisy.jpg"><IMG=20
style=3D"BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0px; BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0px; =
BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0px; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0px"=20
height=3D114 alt=3Ddaisy=20
src=3D"http://osrin.net/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/daisy-thumb.jpg" =
width=3D121=20
border=3D0></A> Cast your mind back to last November and <A=20
href=3D"http://osrin.net/2007/11/14/daisy-gives-an-answer/">you may</A> =
remember=20
Microsoft committing to working with the <A =
href=3D"http://www.daisy.org/">Digital=20
Accessible Information SYstem (DAISY) Consortium</A> to produce a =
translator to=20
their DAISY XML file format (translating WordprocessingML to Daisy =
DTBooks=20
format), this allows anybody with OpenXML files to convert them for use =
with a=20
<A href=3D"http://www.daisy.org/tools/index.shtml">wide array of =
assistive=20
technologies</A>.</P>
<P>I=E2=80=99m pleased to say&nbsp;that as of today the translator is =
available, and=20
will run either in the shell in Windows (right click to translate, just =
like the=20
ODF translator) or will integrate well with Microsoft Office.</P>
<P>From the <A=20
href=3D"http://money.cnn.com/news/newsfeeds/articles/prnewswire/200805070=
301PR_NEWS_USPR_____AQW502.htm"=20
target=3D_blank>Microsoft press release</A>;</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>Microsoft Corp. today joined with industry and advocacy group =
leaders=20
  worldwide to launch new software that will make it easier for anyone =
to create=20
  documents and content that will be accessible for blind and =
print-disabled=20
  individuals. The new =E2=80=9CSave as DAISY XML=E2=80=9D add-in, =
designed for Microsoft Office=20
  Word 2007, Word 2003 and Word XP, will allow users to save Open =
XML-based text=20
  files into DAISY XML, the foundation of the globally accepted DAISY =
standard=20
  for reading and publishing navigable multimedia content (<A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.daisy.org/">http://www.daisy.org/</A>).</P></BLOCKQUOT=
E>
<P>It is also worth noting that the code for the translator is up on =
SourceForge=20
if anybody wants to go take a look for themselves, again from the <A=20
href=3D"http://money.cnn.com/news/newsfeeds/articles/prnewswire/200805070=
301PR_NEWS_USPR_____AQW502.htm"=20
target=3D_blank>press release</A>;&nbsp;</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>The =E2=80=9CSave as DAISY XML=E2=80=9D add-in was created through =
an open source project=20
  with Microsoft, Sonata Software Ltd. and the Digital Accessible =
Information=20
  SYstem (DAISY) Consortium and can be downloaded by Microsoft Office =
Word users=20
  for free at <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.openxmlcommunity.org/daisy">http://www.openxmlcommunit=
y.org/daisy</A>.</P>
  <P>The open source nature of the Open XML to DAISY XML translation =
project=20
  enables technologists to utilize the source code and other resources =
for their=20
  own applications. As Open XML adoption continues to expand across the =
software=20
  industry for use on various platforms, including Linux, Windows, Mac =
OS and=20
  the Palm OS, solution providers interested in creating their own Open =
XML to=20
  DAISY XML translators can reference information available through the=20
  SourceForge open source project site at <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://sourceforge.net/projects/openxml-daisy">http://sourceforge=
.net/projects/openxml-daisy</A>.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><A=20
href=3D"http://www.talkr.com/app/fetch.app?feed_id=3D35963&amp;perma_link=
=3D[http://osrin.net/2008/05/openxmldaisyxml-translator-now-available/]">=
<IMG=20
style=3D"BORDER-TOP-STYLE: none; BORDER-RIGHT-STYLE: none; =
BORDER-LEFT-STYLE: none; BORDER-BOTTOM-STYLE: none"=20
alt=3D"Listen to this article" =
src=3D"http://images.talkr.com/images/speaker_20.gif"=20
border=3D0></A> <A=20
href=3D"http://www.talkr.com/app/fetch.app?feed_id=3D35963&amp;perma_link=
